snippet.title: Arise News Anchor Sommie Maduagwu Dies + Kwara Community Flees Over Insecurity|OjyOkpe
snippet.description:
The ARISE News family is mourning the tragic loss of our beloved colleague, News Anchor, Reporter, and Producer, Somtochukwu Christelle Maduagwu. 

Sommie tragically passed away in the early hours of Monday, September 29, 2025, after an armed robbery incident at her residence in Katampe, Abuja. The police are currently investigating the crime.

After her passing was announced, tributes have poured in including from the Governor of Anambra State, Charles Chukwuma Soludo, and the Minister for Information, Mohammed Idris, among others.

In Kogi State, Barrister Onyesom Peace Udoka was kidnapped alongside her sister, Gift Onyesom, near Lokoja on Friday, September 26th. The reported kidnapping took place just four days after Peace was Called to the Bar in Abuja.

Her abductors are said to be demanding N40 Million Naira to release both victims.

The Nigerian Bar Association has called on the Federal Government and security agencies to swiftly secure the release of its member, describing the incident as “unacceptable and utterly condemnable”. 

In Kwara State, residents of Ajase-Ipo and surrounding communities staged a massive protest, alleging that a recent surge in deadly attacks and bloodletting was orchestrated with the help of a mysterious helicopter.

The community, some of whom were seen fleeing in viral videos, accused security operatives of collusion and abandonment. The state government is now calling for increased military presence in the region.

snippet.title: Israeli forces board Gaza flotilla, detain Greta Thunberg, other activists
snippet.description:
The Israeli navy is arresting activists on board an international aid flotilla,  sailing to the coast of Gaza. 
The activists, are among campaigners on more than 40 boats, aiming to break Israel's maritime blockade of Gaza. 
So far, 13 boats have been stopped and more than 178 people arrested.   
Israel’s Ministry of Foreign Affairs said in a post on X on Wednesday that “several vessels” of the flotilla were “safely stopped and their passengers are being transferred to an Israeli port”.
It wrote that Swedish activist Greta Thunberg, who had been on board the lead ship Alma, “and her friends are safe and healthy”. The ministry also shared a video showing Thunberg.
Several ships were targeted by acts of “active aggression”, it said. “Florida vessel has been deliberately rammed at sea. Yulara, Meteque and others have been targeted with water cannons,” it said on Telegram.

Al Jazeera’s Felix Nyawara reports.
Al Jazeera’s Nida Ibrahim explains what will come next for the activists, who have been arrested.
Huwaida Arraf is an activist, who's part of the Freedom Flotilla, which is currently sailing for Gaza. 
She says the international community is failing in its legal obligations, not just towards the flotilla, but also the Palestinian victims of Israel's genocide
